It is customary to write a letter that spells out the changes in detail 
for those referees who wish to navigate to the new and improved part 
quickly. This often takes the form of a

(
   <quote>
   Ref A wrote: "..."
   </quote>
The revised paper addresses this complaint/suggestion with a new 20 
pages between page 1020 and page 1040.
)+

without addressing at all what you don't care for in the reports. -- 
Matthias



